# LLM configuration -- copy to .env and fill in ONE of the options below.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Option 1: IBM Cloud AI (ICA)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ICA_API_KEY=your-ica-api-key
# ICA_BASE_URL=https://servicesessentials.ibm.com/apis/v3
# ICA_MODEL_ID=global/anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929-v1:0
# ICA_TIMEOUT=300

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Option 2: OpenAI
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-openai-key

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Notes
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# - At least one of ICA_API_KEY or OPENAI_API_KEY IS REQUIRED for the
#   pipeline to run. regrisk is an LLM-driven product; software AI
#   Governance checks (validation/validator.py + core/review.py) run on
#   every LLM output, but there are no parallel non-LLM code paths.
#   See docs/adr/0006-llm-required-and-ai-governance.md.
# - Tests do NOT require an API key -- they use a stub LLM client
#   (tests/_stub_llm.py) that exercises the same code path.
# - The Streamlit app reads .env at startup via python-dotenv (ui/app.py)
#   and shows a blocking error on the Launch buttons if no key is set.
# - Tracing always writes to data/traces.db locally; no cloud setup required.
